<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-925-904  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 925 904.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Nov 27 1989 n343 p139(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Trends: What lies ahead? (transcript of Comdex/Fall 89 conferencesession 'Looking into the Crystal Ball: Watch for These Trends')(transcript)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Zachmann, William F.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Computer-industry executives William F Zachmann, Steve Ballmer,Gordon Eubanks, Bill Joy, Ray Noorda, Fernands Sarrat and MichaelSwavely discuss expected hardware and software trends in the1990s.andP;  Ballmer, of Microsoft Corp, argues that the emergence of astandard platform with a huge installed base was the mostimportant '80s phenomenon; the '90s will see growth in graphicaluser interfaces and suites of multiple applications.andP;  Symantec'sEubanks says that networking will become more and more important;no single operating system will dominate.andP;  Joy, of SunMicrosystems, states that DOS and UNIX will be major platforms inthe year 2000.andP;  Other trends highlighted by the participantsinclude notebook computing; improved price/performance ratios insmall systems; and the emergence of multiple desktop culturesbased on OS/2, DOS, UNIX, and the Macintosh.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TranscriptionConferencesTrade ShowsComdex-FallTrendsComputer IndustrySoftware PublishersFuture of Computing.andO;Person:    Zachmann, William F. (addresses, essays, lectures); Ballmer, Steve(addresses, essays, lectures); Eubanks, Gordon (addresses, essays,lectures); Joy, William N. (addresses, essays, lectures); Noorda,Raymond J. (addresses, essays, lectures); Sarrat, Fernand(addresses, essays, lectures); Swavely, Michael (addresses,essays, lectures).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>